ass=title> Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1>   Level 22 Paladin with good (not fantastic or twinked) armor class but I am dead in seconds when one of those festering hags shows up for the party.  I was playing last night with a fellow Paladin 23rd, a Druid @20, and a 20 Wiz.  I was main puller and brought a Dry Bone Skeleton down the hallway when BANG, she pops up out of nowhere and just overwhelms us.  Felt like I was wearing nothing... LOADING, PLEASE WAIT. <br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
Aaranon<br>
The Rathe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/1/02 8:19:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure exactly what advice you're looking for...<br>
<br>
The festering hags are from the basement, and I think a couple can spawn up on one of the 3rd floor areas.  They are too high level for you to take on, they have a nasty nuke but for their level they have pretty low hit points.  When you are higher level the way to take them down is just to kill them fast, and first if you have a hag + others, because they drop fast, basically high offense low defense mobs.  Paladins can also interrupt them, but if they are too high level you won't be able to cast on them.<br>
<br>
Chances are the hag was the result of a train, Unrest if famous for them.  I've been in the most remote, tucked away corners of Unrest and trains found me.<br>
<br>
Just something you need to accept IMO, I still think Unrest is a fun and rewarding zone even after taking the trains into account.  Just do what you can to minimize their impact (e.g., how to do your best to survive and avoid them, and how to recover quickly when you die from them). <p><BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a>
<BR>
60 Crusader
<BR>
Reign in Power
<BR>
Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthaedson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thaedson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/1/02 9:08:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1> Actually your post was very helpful... I thought they spawned on the first floor and I was pulling from wrong area.... guess the best advise is to RUN when one of these pops right now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 372<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/1/02 10:34:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1> The hags also spawn in the bar and up to the top of the building. Just FYI. <p><font><font size=3><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45984>Balidin</a>,</font> The Evilbasher</b><BR><font color=red><i>Cavalier of Mithaniel</i><BR><font color=white>Apprentice of the Healing Arts of Rodcet Nife<BR>
<BR>
<font color=red><i>Farmond Fistsofdeath</i><font color=white><BR>n00b Monk</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 206<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/1/02 11:20:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1> Those are the 3rd floor areas I was referring to.  Fighting on the ground level should not aggro any hags from their spawn points. <p><BR>
