<BR>
Reign in Power
<BR>
Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvarutiasilvon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varutia Silvon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/2/02 12:43:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1> Train is so common in unrest, it is not uncommon to see hag get train to the first floor.<br>
<br>
Difficult to fight hag at your level, once you got ghoulbane and your first stun at level 30, they are pretty easy.<br>
 <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=177561>Varutia Silvonesit </a><BR>Level 55 Knight<BR>Terris Thule</center><BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 377<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/3/02 10:20:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1> You get stuns at 9 and 15 as well, but yeah, you probably need to be about level 30 to get them to stick reliably. <p><font><font size=3><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45984>Balidin</a>,</font> The Evilbasher</b><BR><font color=red><i>Cavalier of Mithaniel</i><BR><font color=white>Apprentice of the Healing Arts of Rodcet Nife<BR>
<BR>
<font color=red><i>Farmond Fistsofdeath</i><font color=white><BR>n00b Monk</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujaelprayerblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jael Prayerblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/5/02 1:10:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1> Hags are very easy to beat, as long as you dont let them cast.  They dont have a whole lot of Hp, so the trick is trying to kill them without letting them cast.  Time to get your 3 stuns up. <p><center>
<img src="http://www.illumincathari.com/images/profile/jael_sig.jpg">
<center>
Level 56 Paladin of Solusek Ro
<center>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=145351>My Profile</a>
<center>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/5/02 2:04:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1> Jael, I agree that when you're of the level that you can do Unrest basement, hags are easy to beat and paladins are probably just about the best class to put up against them.  <br>
<br>
However if you look at the poster's info his party was in the level 20-23 range.  According to the Allakhazam bestiary hags are level 28-30.  With that level difference it's quite possible that they would be outside the level that you could cast on them.  Even if the casting restriction weren't an issue, I think they'd have a hard time landing their stuns on such a high red con mob. <p><BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a>
<BR>
60 Crusader
<BR>
Reign in Power
<BR>
Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usubataitunare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Subatai Tunare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/6/02 9:23:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1> It's been a long time since I was in unrest, but I remember clearly what we did to beat hags, even in our low 20's. If things haven't changed.<br>
<br>
Hags have a single target dd that they use against you if your running, or out of melee range. They have an ae spell they use when your in melee range, it only hits for like mid 100's if i remember correctly.<br>
<br>
The key here is to close to melee and take her out quick, I'm pretty sure that she will only use the ae if you close to melee range, and once past her damage absorbtion shield she should drop fast.<br>
<br>
So close to melee range fast and take her out, I know this doesn't help the puller, but if you have one show up at your group location this should help.<br>
<br>
Subatai<br>
Level 60 Crusader  <br>
Tunare Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueggolas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eggolas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/6/02 9:27:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1> Ah, the joys of Unrest and Festering Hags.  These darlings are sure to be trained when you least expect ... sort of like the battlemaster ghost on the first floor.<br>
<br>
At early 20s, your best bet is to run for the zone, hitting your TRAIN hotkey (/shout Choo Choo to zone ... run, gate, evac .... get out of the way!)  You won't be able to stick a cease/desist or bash (reliably) to interrupt those 200 pt DD spells coming at you.  <br>
<br>
When you are level 30, plot your revenge.  A good group can take them.  At 45, come back and destroy the basement.  Then do the same to those specs in Oasis that trashed your mid-teen toon.<br>
<br>
Eggolas Moria (45)<br>
Dwarven Paladin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utlaloc00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tlaloc00</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/6/02 11:40:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www2.fwi.com/~thomsons/ltlaloc.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1> you also have to watch the pathing and aggro in there, if you pull from the room that has a named that drops dusty bloodstained glove ( sorry been a long time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), thats on the second floor, you can and probably will aggro the tower.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of wierd pathing issues in the house, as you pull alot you will learn these. I always liked fighting in rooms with window, like the tower and the hand room cause you can bail out and run to the zone if you have to <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
