<b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=37876 ">Coda</a></b><BR>
52 Wanderer<BR>
Tarew Marr<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/7/02 6:08:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/shiken/shinsai1_th.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1> This guide has pretty much all the info you could need for Unrest short of the newer mobs for the second Brell symbol quest:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/pon/articledetails.asp?id=39">eq.castersrealm.com/pon/a....asp?id=39</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I've seen Hags cast 7 different spells:<br>
A single target fire DD, which is their hardest hitter.<br>
A single target ice DD.<br>
A single target magic DD with stun and a big knockback.  This spell is of the all or none resist type.<br>
A single target dispell.<br>
An AOE ice DD spell (at least it looks like ice).<br>
A whimpy 2 point damage shield.<br>
A damage absorber.  This is the first thing they cast when they spawn.<br>
<br>
The AOE only gets used in melee range when facing a group.  The hags are smart emough not to use AOE spells against single targets.  Hags can and will still cast singe target DDs in melee range.<br>
<br>
The damage absorbing spell is easy to get around.  Just hit the hag with a DD spell and it will take the entire rune off, even if the DD only hits for 1 point.<br>
<br>
Hags have around 700 hit points, which is pretty low for their level.  Just pour on the damage and they'll fall. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A> at: 5/7/02 6:14:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthaedson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thaedson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/7/02 6:46:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unrest advise sought</span><hr size=1>   Thanks to all of those who took the time to discuss this.  And I have pulled the extensive guide mentioned in the above post, its a treasure trove!<br>
